<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sony announced pricing and release dates for its PlayStation 5 Wednesday and retailers opened pre-orders of the console one day earlier than expected – creating a buying frenzy among the gaming community.</p>

<p>Gamers around the world ran to their computers, smartphones and tablets to reserve a console, but many were met with broken links, page time outs and the dreaded ‘out of stock’ message.</p>

<p>Major retailers including Amazon, Best Buy, GameStop and Walmart were all sold out within hours, some even in minutes.</p>

<p>The PlayStation 5 was not the only technology up for grabs, as Nivida’s new RTX 3080 graphics card went on sale Thursday, but was also sold out in minutes.</p>

